ACCT 4377 - Oil, Gas and Energy Accounting II
This course is the second of two courses that comprise the study of
accounting principles related to the oil, gas and energy industries. This
course will focus on accounting for asset retirement, sales revenue, tax
accounting, joint interest accounting, conveyances, and oil and gas
disclosures.
Prerequisite: ACCT 4376. Crosslisted as: ACCT 5377.
